Description: Fragment of sub-round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 163, 12? Name Aristombrotidas. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0085.28.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1161)
